{"source_key":"sha256-852da461b9759bc2736926d9891eb9a3","record_index":10087,"record_hash":"sha256:2b21577f6dd342e467fa4a5db87299418a409cf8dcf8727608b8a981abef33eb","timestamp":"2026-05-20T18:46:50.250Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"{\"previous_status\":{\"completed\":\"Mostly enough for a minimal toolset, yes. For a normal same-branch handoff I’d use it like this:\\n\\n```sh\\nbut agentlog sessions branch current --limit 5\\n```\\n\\nPick the obvious latest/main session by timestamp, branch, title, or activity.\\n\\n```sh\\nbut agentlog timeline <session-key> --limit 30\\n```\\n\\nRead the turn list from end backwards until I see: user goal, decisions, files touched, tests run, blockers.\\n\\n```sh\\nbut agentlog records <session-key> --turn <turn-key> --from end --limit 50\\n```\\n\\nOpen the last meaningful turn or two, especially the final assistant summary and any user correction. If the timeline shows earlier important decisions, fetch those turns too.\\n\\nVerdict: enough for catch-up, but barely. The core shape is right: discover sessions, skim timeline, drill into records.\\n\\nWhat’s missing:\\n\\n- `sessions branch current` or default-to-current-branch behavior. Making agents spell the branch is needless friction.\\n- Session summaries in `sessions` output: title, last user ask, last assistant status, changed files, test status, timestamp. Without this, agents will over-fetch timelines.\\n- Timeline entries need record counts and turn metadata: user/assistant/tool, timestamp, short summary, maybe files touched. Otherwise `timeline` is just a pager into mystery meat.\\n- `records` needs stable ordering and clear indices. If `--from end --limit 50` means reverse chronological, say so; if not, agents will mess this up.\\n- A way to list “related but not same branch” sessions would help, but it can wait. Same branch covers the common laptop-to-laptop case.\\n\\nToo complex:\\n\\n- `--from start|end|<index>` is okay, but slightly fussy. I’d prefer `--before <index>` / `--after <index>` eventually. For v1, it’s fine.\\n- Three entity filters on `sessions` are fine if branch/review/change are first-class GitButler concepts. If not, start with branch only.\\n\\nRedundant:\\n\\n- Nothing major. `timeline` and `records` are not redundant if timeline is a skim view and records is raw/detail view.\\n\\nOne concrete improvement I’d make: let `timeline` include the last assistant message excerpt per turn. That alone makes this usable without inventing a magic handoff command.\"}}","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T18:46:50.250Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}